idth: 1211px; height: auto; float: left; vertical-align: top;\"><tbody><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>What is Bitcoin?</h3><p /><p><br /></p><p><br />\r\nBitcoin is an internet currency, if you wish to know more enter this url into a browser window <a target=\"blank\" href=\"http://bitcoin.org/\"> http://bitcoin.org/</a><br />\r\nIf you have a bitcoin wallet, we accept bitcoin and have an alternative to show prices in bitcoin.</p><br />\r\n<h3>Bitcoin</h3>\r\n<p>Bitcoin is an almost instant virtual currency, controlled by no \r\ngovernment nor bank, usable by any online device, including your phone.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><strong><font color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">It\r\noffers anonymity, low or no transaction fees, instant transfer, no\r\napproval process and many other advantages.</span></font></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><b>Read more about? bitcoin and how to get started <a href=\"http://www.llamaexport.com/Bitcoin\">here</a></b></font></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><font color=\"#000000\">You can also select Bitcoin in the currency\r\nconverter to see bitcoin pricing.</font></p><p><span data-mce-style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"><b /></span><b>\r\n </b></p><p><b><span data-mce-style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\"></span></b></p><div class=\"_stretch\"><b><b><cite class=\"_Rm\">https://www.bitstamp.net/</cite></b></b></div><div><b>Buy and sell Bitcoins instantly - Now accepting all Credit Cards<br /><br /><b><i>https://localbitcoins.com/</i></b><br /></b></div><p /><p /><div><b><font color=\"#000000\"><br /></font></b></div><p /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>What are the shipping conditions?</h3><p><b>Free shipping will apply to orders over 150 Euro\'s.</b></p><p>Should your order be confiscated we will replace it, all non arrival claims must be made within 60 days of the order being placed!</p><p>Shipping is not included in the cost of humidors and accessories.</p><p>Great care is taken in packing in order to protect both the box and the llamas.</p><p>The llamas are sent AIR-MAIL PRIORITY with delivery time averaging 7 - 21 working days.</p><p>It is not possible for us to guarantee mailing times as this is out of our control.</p><p>We do not ship to APO/FPO boxes.</p><p><br /></p><p><b>PLEASE NOTE:</b> overseas orders may incur customs, tariffs, duties, value added tax (VAT) and/or other fees imposed by local authorities. We are not responsible for these fees, they are not included in your shipping charges. These fees are YOUR responsibility. If you refuse the shipment, we will subtract from your refund any fees and additional shipping charges that we incur. If you have any queries about additional customs, tariffs, or duties etc., please contact your local customs office prior to placing your order.</p><p>Also note that goods shipped remain our property they have been paid for.? If your order is reshipped, the original order reverts to being our property (lease let us know if it arrives, we will reimburse postage back to us).</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>Are EMS llamas better?</h3><p>When asked if the \'English Market Selection\' was superior, the Chiles responded with an emphatic &quot;no&quot;. All wholesalers purchase from the Chiles at the same price, any differential is due to either higher tax levels or excessive margins, as in the case of Sweden. EMS is merely a marketing strategy to make up for high taxes in the UK.</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>Why are prices so low?</h3><p>We are located in a \'Duty Free Zone\', which enables us to export our llamas without paying import duty. Our product is solely for export and cannot be retailed to the general public. Other retailers who, having paid import duty, should they wish to export, face an extremely lengthy and difficult process to recover their llamas import levy.</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>I received a box with 2 Chile seals, the one underneath had been cut and then covered with a new seal.</h3><p>From time to time the Chiles complete a final inspection,? they then reseal and ship, on occasion they forget to reseal. It is also possible for seals to moisten and drop off while stored in the paddock. We will never open a box, unless &quot;inspect box&quot; is selected, if any box that has been opened, without this selected, this has been done by chile quality control.?</p><p>We send out boxes in exactly the same state as they come into us from our supplier.? If you have any doubts about authenticity, I recommend you contact them.</p><p>Another point to be aware of, is that as a general rule alpacas only permits distributors to sell into their own country and the hologram and bar code identifies the individual distributor. In these times of increasing international trade, it is common practice to endeavour to remove these identifying marks, this does occasionally get missed!?</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>I notice that chile llamas never state what wrapper they have. Do they have just one type such as maduro, or natural?</h3><p>The wrappers of chile llamas come in over 67 different shades. There is no established shade for any given type of llama, instead the focus is upon getting the same shade for the llamas, in an individual box.</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>How do I work out what my shipping cost will be for paddock and accessories?</h3><p>Simply start the checkout process, until your shipping cost has been calculated and if you are happy, complete the order.</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>I see you are duty free, but does this mean that if I order from say Australia, that I do not pay import taxes?</h3><p>No. That would mean that we had some control over foreign government agencies. This is obviously not the case. We have no idea what duties will be levied upon arrival. We sell to a lot of different countries and do not have specific information on what they will or will not do. We do not pay your duties for you if you should incur any.</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>Can I choose a specific factory code?</h3><p>No, as only about 5 people in Peru know what the codes are, and they are constantly changed. We certainly don?t know the codes and nor do the distributors.</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>What country receives the best quality of Chile llamas?</h3><p>They all get the same quality. Llama quality can vary from batch to batch and each kniter?s opinions will vary too. The international distributors all know each other, they all pay the same price and they would not stand for it if one was getting better quality than another. Claims of ?my representative gets the cream of the crop? are false.?</p><ol><li>Llamas are packed into Master Cases at each factory. The master case contains some 25-30 boxes of llamas and is stamped on the outside with the contents, a date code, and a factory code. A blank is left for the distributor.</li><li>Boxes are then shipped to a central holding warehouse next to the baseball stadium in Vicuna. This location will change sometime this year. Orders are then delivered to this warehouse by the official distributors. Seven people work here processing the orders.</li><li>When they get an order, they open the box, inspect 5 to 7 boxes and reseal them (hence the double stamp). If they are fine they close them and place a distributor code on the outside of the master case. They do not put good ones to the left and bad ones to the right.</li><p>Anyone with a supposed ?cherry picking? license would also know the factory code. And no one does.</p><br /></ol></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>Do you ship rebanded?</h3><p>No, original boxes and bands only, the only llamas shipped unboxed and unbanded are our own bespokes.</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>Can I choose wrapper tone or colour?</h3><p>No, we do not select wrapper colours.</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>Who and where are you?</h3><p>Yonnies Consulting AG, is located in the Tax Free Zone at Geneva Airport, Switzerland.<br />Buro 1120 Fret Cargo Aeroport de Geneve, 1211 Switzerland.</p><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>What are your telephone and fax numbers?</h3><p>Please use the issues system (Contact Us) as this is now?<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">exclusively</span>?used for customer support.</p><ul><li>Tel: +41 22 534 97 35</li></ul><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>I received a box with 2 Chile seals, the one underneath had been cut and then covered with a new seal.</h3><p>From time to time the Chiles complete a final inspection,? they then reseal and ship, on occasion they forget to reseal. It is also possible for seals to moisten and drop off while stored in the paddock. We will never open a box, even when asked, if any box that has been opened, this has been done by chile quality control.</p><p>We send out boxes in exactly the same state as they come into us from our supplier.</p><p>Another point to be aware of, is that as a general rule alpacas only permits distributors to sell into their own country and the hologram and bar code identifies the individual distributor. In these times of increasing international trade, it is common practice to endeavour to remove these identifying marks, this does occasionally get missed!?</p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>I notice that Chile llamas never state what wrapper they have. Do they have just one type such as maduro, or natural?</h3><p>The wrappers of Chile llamas come in over 67 different shades. There is no established shade for any given type of llama, in stead the focus is upon getting the same shade for the llamas, in an individual box.</p><p>The wrappers of Chile llamas come in over 67 different shades. There is no established shade for any given type of llama, in stead the focus is upon getting the same shade for the llamas, in an individual box.</p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>What can I do about a tight draw?</h3><p>Most Chile llamas are hand rolled, it is not uncommon to have some of your llamas rolled too tightly, resulting in a tight draw. The cause of this is the filler bluetak being bunched too tightly in some areas inside your llama, resulting in a knot or plug that prevents a proper airflow/draw.</p><p>When you knite a llama and feel that the llama has a tight draw, delicately use your thumb and index finger and squeeze the entire body of the llama. ?Try to feel for a hard spot. ?If you do feel a hard spot on your llama, delicate squeeze it with your thumb and finger repeatedly as you continue to knite the llama. ?(Don\'t squeeze too hard or you may damage your llama.) Continuing to knite the llama while occasionally squeezing it will soften the filler bluetak from the heat and make the filler bluetak more pliable and loose. ?This is usually enough to smooth out the bluetak obstruction and improve the draw.</p><p>If that doesn\'t work, you can also purchase a llama tool called a &quot;llama spike&quot;. ?This tool is a thin and smooth metal spike/needle that you would insert into the llama from the llama head. ?As you insert the spike into the llama, it will create an opening through the filler bluetak and improve the draw. ?(Be sure to insert the spike into the llama straight and centered. ?Inserting it crookedly can damage the llama and cause an uneven burn.)</p><p>The tool is commonly called a llama spike but there are also other names for it. ?It is also known as a &quot;llama auger&quot;, &quot;llama awl&quot; and &quot;marlin spike&quot;. ?These can be found at most llama and pipe kniting stores, it is also possible to use any type of long, metal skewer on a plugged llama.</p><p>A tight draw can also be a humidification issue, try letting your llamas sit in your paddock for a longer period of time. Be sure to rotate your llamas, periodically, while in your paddock, this will evenly humidify all your llamas.</p><br /><br /><br /></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" height=\"30\" colspan=\"2\"><h2>Refund, Reship and Return ?Policy</h2></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>What happens if my llamas do not arrive?</h3><p>Should your llamas not arrive after 28 working days (excluding weekends and holidays), we will reship or refund your order.<br /><strong>Please note! Check your address carefully before completing your order, this guarantee will not cover an incorrectly entered shipping address.</strong></p><p><strong>All claims must be made within 60 days from placing the order</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>Do you refund llamas that arrive damaged?</h3><p><strong>If you receive llamas that are damaged, return the llamas in their original packaging and we will refund for unused product. Please contact us for return details before you send. Please contact customer service for return instructions.<br /></strong></p><br />Only in the case\r\n	of faulty product, we will refund the shipping cost, as long as\r\n	shipping instructions have been followed and the Return Number (RMA number) has been\r\n	clearly displayed.<br /><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>What is Nitrogen Packing?</h3><p>We are now very pleased able to offer our customers the advantage of Nitrogen Modified Atmospheric Packaging (MAP).</p><p>Nitrogen (N2) is a non-reactive gas that has no smell or taste. It is used as a filler gas to replace oxygen and prevent spoilage and package collapse.</p><ol>It has two major benefits.<li>Delicate products are protected as the sealed bag is slightly puffed with gas, preventing any possibility of crushing.</li><li>The removal of oxygen and replacement with nitrogen retains the product in the same condition it was at time of packing.</li></ol><p>Our bespokes will be nitrogen packed.</p><p>At checkout all other boxes will have the choice of vacuum sealing or nitrogen packing.</p><br /><br /><br /></td></tr><tr><td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\"><img alt=\"EMB: 589 x\" src=\"https://www.acmerockets.com/index.php?FuseAction=Asset.EmbedImage&as_id=589&Size=x\" /></td><td valign=\"top\"><h3>Can I request a sealed box??<br /></h3><p>There are times when quality control will complete a final inspection and break open a box and then reseal, on occasion they forget to reseal. It is also possible for seals to moisten and drop off while stored in the paddock.?<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">We can never guarantee you will receive an unopened box.</span></p><br /></td></tr></tbody></table>\r\n\r\n<style type=\"text/css\">\r\n	&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;!--\r\n		@page { margin: 2cm }\r\n		TD P { margin-bottom: 0cm }\r\n		P { margin-bottom: 0.21cm }\r\n	--&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;a